# PureTask Documentation Rules (Must Follow)

## Canonical Docs Only
- The ONLY "active" documentation lives in:
  - docs/active/README.md
  - docs/active/SETUP.md
  - docs/active/ARCHITECTURE.md
  - docs/active/RUNBOOK.md
  - docs/active/DEPLOYMENT.md
  - docs/active/TROUBLESHOOTING.md
  - docs/active/DECISIONS.md

## Do NOT create new markdown files
- Never create new *.md files anywhere except:
  - docs/active/
  - docs/archive/

## Where to put new info
- If it's a setup/run instruction → append to docs/active/SETUP.md
- If it's how the system fits together → append to docs/active/ARCHITECTURE.md
- If it's ops/debugging → append to docs/active/RUNBOOK.md
- If it's deployment/railway/prod → append to docs/active/DEPLOYMENT.md
- If it's "known issue" troubleshooting → append to docs/active/TROUBLESHOOTING.md
- If it's a choice we made and why → append to docs/active/DECISIONS.md

## Archive policy
- Historical notes, experiments, logs, old plans go in docs/archive/raw/
- Never delete raw history. Only move it to archive.
